%spark
import org.apache.spark.mllib.linalg.Vectors
import org.apache.spark.mllib.clustering.KMeans
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._
import org.apache.spark.mllib.util.MLUtils

// load file and remove header
val data = sc.textFile("data/housing_data.csv")
//val data = MLUtils.loadLibSVMFile(sc, "data/housing_data.csv")
val header = data.first
println(header)
val rows = data.filter(l => l != header)

// comma separator split
val allSplit = rows.map(line => line.split(","))
// map parts to case class
val housingDataRDD = allSplit.map( p => HousingData( p(0).trim.toInt, p(1).trim.toInt, p(2).trim.toDouble, p(3).trim.toDouble, p(4).trim.toDouble, p(5).trim.toInt, p(6).trim.toInt, p(7).trim.toDouble, p(8).trim.toInt))
housingDataRDD.cache()
housingDataRDD.saveToGrid()

val splits = housingDataRDD.randomSplit(Array(0.7, 0.3))
val (trainingData, testData) = (splits(0), splits(1))
